1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
The Greatest Marriage

2
00:00:06,954 --> 00:00:09,853
<i>Episode 11</i>

3
00:00:09,854 --> 00:00:13,502
<i>[3 Years Later]</i>

4
00:00:13,503 --> 00:00:15,383
Cue!

5
00:00:15,384 --> 00:00:17,772
This is '24 Hours of Hope' and
I'm with the rescue team right now!

6
00:00:17,773 --> 00:00:20,437
I'm Cha Ki Young, your reporter
starting today.

7
00:00:20,438 --> 00:00:24,808
Right now, the rescue team is on its way
to save a person who fell while hiking.

8
00:00:25,841 --> 00:00:30,383
The patient's life depends upon how fast
they will be able to get to the hospital.

9
00:00:30,384 --> 00:00:31,814
Cut!

10
00:00:31,815 --> 00:00:34,531
Let's get on the helicopter!

11
00:00:35,278 --> 00:00:38,409
- You want me to ride in the helicopter?
- Of course!

12
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:40,663
No one told me that I had
to ride in the helicopter!

13
00:00:40,664 --> 00:00:44,009
You have to be in the action
if you want the full story!

14
00:00:44,010 --> 00:00:47,671
One of the rescue team members will help,
so don't worry and get in!

15
00:00:56,445 --> 00:00:58,426
I don't think I can do it!

16
00:00:58,427 --> 00:01:00,596
You don't have a choice!
We have to record this show!

17
00:01:00,597 --> 00:01:02,490
Are you going to get in or not?

18
00:01:02,491 --> 00:01:06,962
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

19
00:01:09,636 --> 00:01:11,056
Hello?

20
00:01:11,575 --> 00:01:13,819
Yes, Director?

21
00:01:13,820 --> 00:01:17,693
I'm not in a position
to talk on the phone right now!

22
00:01:19,205 --> 00:01:20,768
Today?

23
00:01:20,769 --> 00:01:23,541
- I'm going to be late again today.
- What are you doing?

24
00:01:23,542 --> 00:01:26,187
Please take good care of Dan for me!

25
00:01:26,188 --> 00:01:28,083
I'm sorry!

26
00:01:31,788 --> 00:01:34,981
This is Channel Korea with your
nine o'clock news. My name is Jo Eun Cha...

27
00:01:34,982 --> 00:01:36,839
and Kang Ha Ni.

28
00:01:39,531 --> 00:01:41,226
Here is our first story.

29
00:01:41,227 --> 00:01:43,378
The three most powerful men in North Korea

30
00:01:43,379 --> 00:01:45,399
will be attending the closing ceremony
of the Asian Games.

31
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:49,806
Talks between the the North and South
are more active than ever.

32
00:01:49,807 --> 00:01:53,346
Reporter Kim Hyung Joon has
the full story from the Blue House.

33
00:01:54,064 --> 00:01:57,071
<i>The possibility of peace between
North and South Korea...</i>

34
00:01:58,018 --> 00:02:01,203
What are we to do if reunification happens?

35
00:02:01,778 --> 00:02:05,270
- You hate reunification?
- I totally hate it.

36
00:02:05,271 --> 00:02:08,498
We'll have to live with
those poor North Koreans.

37
00:02:09,853 --> 00:02:13,302
<i>Also, why are North Korea and
South Korea considered one country?</i>

38
00:02:13,303 --> 00:02:17,582
<i>Americans think we look the same
as the Japanese.</i>

39
00:02:17,583 --> 00:02:21,322
She's an anchor. Why is she so clueless?

40
00:02:21,323 --> 00:02:24,121
She's studied in America
since she was young.

41
00:02:24,122 --> 00:02:26,164
And she was singled out
to be an announcer.

42
00:02:26,165 --> 00:02:28,211
She only looks Korean.

43
00:02:28,212 --> 00:02:30,458
Internally, she's completely American.

44
00:02:30,459 --> 00:02:32,502
My daughter is also studying abroad.

45
00:02:32,503 --> 00:02:35,060
And I'm afraid she's going
to turn out like her.

46
00:02:35,061 --> 00:02:38,150
Director, Eun Cha has changed.

47
00:02:38,151 --> 00:02:42,561
In the past, he would've trampled
all over girls like Kang Ha Ni on the spot.

48
00:02:42,562 --> 00:02:47,018
That punk. He's just playing nice because
the general elections are coming up.

49
00:02:47,589 --> 00:02:50,046
You honestly think people can change?

50
00:02:53,908 --> 00:02:57,372
Ma'am, I'm busy right now.
I'll call you later!

51
00:02:57,373 --> 00:02:59,609
What the heck are you doing right now?
Move!

52
00:03:01,263 --> 00:03:03,271
Seriously, I'm going nuts here!

53
00:03:06,631 --> 00:03:08,607
Transfer him to the operating room!

54
00:03:10,165 --> 00:03:11,572
Cut!

55
00:03:11,573 --> 00:03:13,961
This sucks!
Why did you bring a woman along?

56
00:03:14,792 --> 00:03:19,378
We'll refuse to cooperate
if you keep getting in our way like this!

57
00:03:23,506 --> 00:03:25,821
You're not even remotely interested
in the patient's condition.

58
00:03:25,822 --> 00:03:28,017
You're only concerned about your child!

59
00:03:28,559 --> 00:03:30,208
I'm sorry.

60
00:03:30,209 --> 00:03:34,134
The daycare closes at seven and
it's past nine o'clock right now.

61
00:03:34,135 --> 00:03:36,942
The teacher kept calling to say
she was closing.

62
00:03:38,673 --> 00:03:42,828
Then quit your job and
watch your kid instead, okay?

63
00:03:42,829 --> 00:03:45,742
I hear this isn't the first time
you screwed over a recording!

64
00:03:45,743 --> 00:03:47,674
Your words are a bit harsh.

65
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:51,803
You think my words are harsh?
What about your actions?

66
00:03:53,229 --> 00:03:55,330
Let's just call it quits.

67
00:03:55,331 --> 00:03:57,773
Throw away every recording
with Cha Ki Young in it

68
00:03:57,774 --> 00:04:00,194
and let's start all over
by casting someone else.

69
00:04:00,195 --> 00:04:02,088
Let's wrap it up.

70
00:04:13,719 --> 00:04:17,865
Ma'am, I just finished wrapping up.
How is Dan doing?

71
00:04:18,868 --> 00:04:20,976
We've headed over to commercial.

72
00:04:24,479 --> 00:04:26,553
Hey, Gap Soo.

73
00:04:27,377 --> 00:04:29,048
Kang Ha Ni?

74
00:04:29,771 --> 00:04:31,843
A fashion show MC?

75
00:04:32,583 --> 00:04:35,827
Why would a news anchor
host a fashion show? Hang up!

76
00:04:37,485 --> 00:04:40,015
Why didn't you ask for my opinion first?

77
00:04:40,578 --> 00:04:44,344
I didn't ask for your opinion
when you were placed next to me.

78
00:04:44,345 --> 00:04:47,931
I'm not going to ask for your opinion
when you get fired, either.

79
00:04:47,932 --> 00:04:49,867
You have a problem with that?

80
00:05:01,937 --> 00:05:03,550
I'm so sorry!

81
00:05:04,042 --> 00:05:08,222
He kept waiting for you at this spot
and he just fell asleep.

82
00:05:08,223 --> 00:05:11,499
I'm so sorry. My work ended
much later than I expected.

83
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:13,035
I'll take him.

84
00:05:14,559 --> 00:05:18,693
Does Dan have other family members?
His grandmother perhaps?

85
00:05:18,694 --> 00:05:20,507
He doesn't have one.

86
00:05:20,508 --> 00:05:22,904
It would be nice if he did.

87
00:05:22,905 --> 00:05:26,175
Dan is a little different
from the other children.

88
00:05:26,176 --> 00:05:27,800
In what way?

89
00:05:27,801 --> 00:05:30,864
Boys like to get physical when they play.

90
00:05:30,865 --> 00:05:32,987
But Dan's always playing quietly by himself.

91
00:05:32,988 --> 00:05:35,252
He doesn't know how to approach people

92
00:05:35,253 --> 00:05:38,297
and I'm wondering if it's because
he only spends time with you.

93
00:05:38,298 --> 00:05:42,404
Those symptoms usually appear
in children that lack attention.

94
00:05:43,628 --> 00:05:46,149
He's been a quiet child
ever since he was born.

95
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:47,999
There are children who are
outgoing by nature

96
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,865
but there are also children
who are introverts.

97
00:05:49,866 --> 00:05:52,486
It's not like I'm going to raise him
to be a professional athlete.

98
00:05:52,487 --> 00:05:57,773
I'm going to raise a child who
loves to read instead of a dumb jock.

99
00:06:51,158 --> 00:06:55,199
All right then, list off
all the clans in our family.

100
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:57,493
Which generation should
I start from, Father?

101
00:06:57,494 --> 00:06:58,912
Start with the 25th.

102
00:06:59,766 --> 00:07:03,686
Jae Shin Kyu from the 25th generation,
Yong San Jong from the 26th generation...

103
00:07:03,687 --> 00:07:09,018
Ho Soo Soon from the 27th generation,
Im Joo Sang from the 28th generation...

104
00:07:09,019 --> 00:07:12,970
Yeol Yong Hee from the 29th generation,
Shi Joon from the 30th generation...

105
00:07:12,971 --> 00:07:17,476
Ho Heum Goo from the 31st generation,
Hae Yoon Han from the 32nd generation...

106
00:07:17,477 --> 00:07:22,897
Shik Geun Kwon from the 33rd generation,
Hon Eung from the 34th generation.

107
00:07:26,076 --> 00:07:27,926
Good job.

108
00:07:28,848 --> 00:07:31,052
Now, read these characters.

109
00:07:31,053 --> 00:07:34,701
Park Eun Chil?

110
00:07:35,405 --> 00:07:37,800
This is the name of Tae Yun's son.

111
00:07:40,593 --> 00:07:42,439
Good.

112
00:07:43,528 --> 00:07:45,968
Sons are precious in our family.

113
00:07:45,969 --> 00:07:48,602
During my father's lifetime,
a monk told us

114
00:07:48,602 --> 00:07:50,876
our lives would be shortened
if we used a family name.

115
00:07:50,877 --> 00:07:54,177
That's why I didn't give
Tae Yun a common family name.

116
00:07:54,178 --> 00:07:59,490
But I've decided to begin that tradition
again, starting with Tae Yun's son.

117
00:08:00,118 --> 00:08:02,167
Thank you, Father.

118
00:08:02,168 --> 00:08:06,533
Since the short lifespan was
taken care of with your miscarriage...

119
00:08:06,534 --> 00:08:10,350
I'm sure we won't have another child
who will die early again.

120
00:08:14,107 --> 00:08:16,208
Did something good happen?

121
00:08:16,209 --> 00:08:21,455
Mother, Father came up with
a name for our future son.

122
00:08:22,038 --> 00:08:24,195
What's the name?

123
00:08:24,847 --> 00:08:27,891
Park Eun Chil.

124
00:08:27,892 --> 00:08:30,057
Eun Chil?

125
00:08:33,272 --> 00:08:35,087
That's a fine name.

126
00:08:39,868 --> 00:08:44,676
She remembered every family name
when no else could.

127
00:08:44,677 --> 00:08:47,566
We accepted a daughter-in-law
without a son to show for it.

128
00:08:47,567 --> 00:08:49,491
In that sense, it's comfortable.

129
00:08:55,974 --> 00:08:59,537
This the picture
he sent me last night, Mother.

130
00:09:01,284 --> 00:09:03,143
Where is this now?

131
00:09:03,144 --> 00:09:05,778
It's a small restaurant in Kyoto, Japan.

132
00:09:05,779 --> 00:09:08,063
He was in Czechoslovakia two months ago.

133
00:09:08,064 --> 00:09:12,431
He said he's going to study every cuisine
in the world before he returns.

134
00:09:16,538 --> 00:09:18,994
You must keep this a secret
from your father-in-law.

135
00:09:18,995 --> 00:09:22,652
For all he knows,
Tae Yun is still studying overseas.

136
00:09:22,653 --> 00:09:24,827
Understood?

137
00:09:24,828 --> 00:09:27,173
Yes, Mother.

138
00:09:33,099 --> 00:09:37,655
<i>When I open my eyes,
I find this small child next to me.</i>

139
00:09:37,656 --> 00:09:40,336
<i>I still find it unfamiliar and fascinating.</i>

140
00:09:41,112 --> 00:09:44,697
<i>I never relied on anyone
from the moment I was born.</i>

141
00:09:44,698 --> 00:09:49,720
<i>But now, my whole life
revolves around this child.</i>

142
00:09:58,225 --> 00:10:01,173
- Hey, Mom.
- Is the child growing well?

143
00:10:01,174 --> 00:10:04,168
- Yeah.
- How about work?

144
00:10:04,892 --> 00:10:06,896
Well, it's coming along.

145
00:10:06,897 --> 00:10:09,308
I know it's tough trying to work
while taking care of him.

146
00:10:09,309 --> 00:10:13,333
There's no need to suffer like that.
I said I'd take care of him for you.

147
00:10:13,334 --> 00:10:15,578
I left so we could live together.

148
00:10:15,579 --> 00:10:18,533
That would be meaningless
if I left him in your care.

149
00:10:19,055 --> 00:10:23,426
Also, I won't be able to work more
if I drop him off.

150
00:10:23,427 --> 00:10:25,291
Don't worry, Mom.

151
00:10:25,292 --> 00:10:30,105
Alright. Call me right away
if something happens, okay?

152
00:10:30,106 --> 00:10:31,801
I will, Mom.

153
00:10:37,289 --> 00:10:38,612
Hey, baby.

154
00:10:40,599 --> 00:10:42,281
Baby.

155
00:10:42,282 --> 00:10:44,421
It's time to wake up.

156
00:10:44,422 --> 00:10:48,764
- I don't want to.
- You have to wake up now!

157
00:10:48,765 --> 00:10:50,607
I don't want to.

158
00:10:51,307 --> 00:10:53,194
Let's see here.

159
00:10:54,345 --> 00:10:59,063
You didn't have an accident today!
Good boy, come here!

160
00:11:07,352 --> 00:11:09,091
Mom.

161
00:11:09,092 --> 00:11:13,277
- Yes?
- Can't you come and pick me up today?

162
00:11:13,278 --> 00:11:14,637
Why?

163
00:11:14,638 --> 00:11:20,018
My other friends have their
mom or dad come to pick them up

164
00:11:20,019 --> 00:11:22,342
and I was the only that didn't.

165
00:11:30,613 --> 00:11:35,961
In the past, baby bones were discovered
in many of the royal palaces.

166
00:11:35,962 --> 00:11:39,315
When night came, the only man was the king.

167
00:11:39,316 --> 00:11:44,220
The palace maids would compete fiercely
to put their baby on the throne.

168
00:11:46,509 --> 00:11:53,177
They say this yongbong stew
gave energy to the king back then.

169
00:12:03,123 --> 00:12:06,104
<i>Here are the pictures
of the child you requested.</i>

170
00:12:07,282 --> 00:12:09,517
<i>I've only been taking pictures
for the past three years.</i>

171
00:12:09,518 --> 00:12:11,878
<i>When do you want me to take action?</i>

172
00:12:13,334 --> 00:12:16,837
<i>Just wait and always be ready.</i>

173
00:12:40,990 --> 00:12:43,830
- You stupid bastard.
- Hey!

174
00:12:43,831 --> 00:12:45,467
Did you come for a recording?

175
00:12:45,468 --> 00:12:47,382
I hear you're running for election
to the National Assembly?

176
00:12:47,383 --> 00:12:49,349
Please help me.

177
00:12:49,350 --> 00:12:53,309
I promise to support you on your comeback
if I get elected to the National Assembly.

178
00:12:53,310 --> 00:12:55,260
You won't get elected
no matter how hard you try.

179
00:12:55,261 --> 00:12:56,725
You think anyone can be a politician?

180
00:12:56,726 --> 00:12:58,630
You did it too.
Why are you speaking ill of me?

181
00:12:58,631 --> 00:13:02,025
Didn't you feel anything when you saw me
get kicked out of the National Assembly?

182
00:13:02,831 --> 00:13:06,009
You and I are alpha males to the core.

183
00:13:06,010 --> 00:13:07,656
And we can't live our lives
hiding that fact.

184
00:13:07,657 --> 00:13:09,767
Sixty percent of the voters are women.

185
00:13:09,768 --> 00:13:12,265
How can sexist men like us be elected?

186
00:13:12,797 --> 00:13:16,923
One wrong word makes
the both of us look bad.

187
00:13:16,924 --> 00:13:19,052
Even so, you think we'll be able
to throw away that alpha mentality?

188
00:13:19,053 --> 00:13:21,630
That's the very thing that
our fathers passed down.

189
00:13:21,631 --> 00:13:24,267
'Men are the heavens
and women are the Earth.'

190
00:13:25,256 --> 00:13:26,841
You may have failed

191
00:13:26,842 --> 00:13:30,113
but I have a trump card that will
help me rack up all the female voters.

192
00:13:30,114 --> 00:13:31,400
What is it?

193
00:13:31,401 --> 00:13:35,495
I'm an alpha male disguised as a feminist.

194
00:13:35,496 --> 00:13:39,421
Let's just say I'm a wolf posing
as an innocent sheep.

195
00:13:41,988 --> 00:13:47,514
I only picked women with bad performance
evaluations who have children.

196
00:13:47,515 --> 00:13:50,349
Cha Ki Young is ranked
number one on the list?

197
00:13:50,350 --> 00:13:54,199
She's been ranked last for the past
three years with her evaluations.

198
00:13:54,736 --> 00:13:56,215
Let me take a look.

199
00:14:01,810 --> 00:14:04,729
Goodness, how did she come to be like this?

200
00:14:05,624 --> 00:14:10,326
All the decent ones are gone,
and only the useless ones are left.

201
00:14:10,327 --> 00:14:13,935
Who would stay when everyone's
salaries were cut by 30 percent?

202
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:17,744
Five of our ace reporters quit
just last month alone.

203
00:14:19,076 --> 00:14:21,012
Do you have something in mind?

204
00:14:21,983 --> 00:14:24,681
We have no choice if we want
to save the company.

205
00:14:24,682 --> 00:14:28,015
Get rid of all the useless
people like Cha Ki Young

206
00:14:28,016 --> 00:14:30,932
and give all the decent workers
their original wages back.

207
00:14:32,415 --> 00:14:34,526
Is that the only solution?

208
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:39,416
I hear Cha Ki Young is struggling
to take care of her child.

209
00:14:40,758 --> 00:14:44,181
The company is in danger
because you're so soft-hearted!

210
00:14:44,182 --> 00:14:46,130
Ho Pyung, you need to toughen up!

211
00:14:53,620 --> 00:14:58,168
Money has been tight ever since our
wages were cut by 30 percent.

212
00:14:58,169 --> 00:15:01,138
I'm pretty much at zero after
I pay the monthly loan interest.

213
00:15:01,139 --> 00:15:03,739
I thought your ex-husband
was helping you with that?

214
00:15:03,740 --> 00:15:06,318
Nurse Jung is the office wife.

215
00:15:06,319 --> 00:15:08,437
She has a tight hold on
the hospital's purse strings.

216
00:15:08,438 --> 00:15:11,216
I'm even paying for all the
apartment maintenance fees on my own.

217
00:15:11,716 --> 00:15:13,589
It pisses me off the more I think about it.

218
00:15:13,590 --> 00:15:17,354
Hurry up and end it with him
while Ara is studying overseas.

219
00:15:22,715 --> 00:15:25,657
It's been three years since we put our home
on the market and he still won't leave.

220
00:15:25,658 --> 00:15:27,905
Have you ever heard of
a woman that still lives with

221
00:15:27,906 --> 00:15:30,944
her ex-husband just because
their place hasn't been sold?

222
00:15:31,790 --> 00:15:35,586
Raising a child is so expensive.

223
00:15:36,099 --> 00:15:39,562
I realized that money is more important
than love when it comes to raising a child.

224
00:15:43,207 --> 00:15:44,597
Hello?

225
00:15:44,598 --> 00:15:47,978
Cha Ki Young, this is the news station.
We need to talk.

226
00:15:47,979 --> 00:15:49,396
Right now?

227
00:15:49,397 --> 00:15:50,815
It's important.

228
00:15:54,763 --> 00:15:58,147
I need to go to the news station.
He says it's important.

229
00:15:58,148 --> 00:16:01,249
He probably wants you
to fill in for a minor program again.

230
00:16:02,568 --> 00:16:04,278
What are you going to do about Dan?

231
00:16:04,279 --> 00:16:06,648
I can't drop him off anywhere
on this short of notice.

232
00:16:06,649 --> 00:16:08,668
I guess I'll just have to take him with me.

233
00:16:10,018 --> 00:16:12,463
Mom, where are we?

234
00:16:12,464 --> 00:16:15,179
It's the news station I work for.

235
00:16:21,343 --> 00:16:22,947
Let's go in.

236
00:16:29,755 --> 00:16:32,701
Don't go anywhere and stay right here.
I'll be right back, okay?

237
00:16:32,702 --> 00:16:34,057
Okay.

238
00:16:42,469 --> 00:16:43,822
Hello.

239
00:16:43,823 --> 00:16:45,432
- You're here.
- Yes.

240
00:16:45,433 --> 00:16:46,944
