but I have nothing decent to wear.

489
00:33:09,669 --> 00:33:12,670
I don't have clothes that are
appropriate for a fashion show.

490
00:33:12,671 --> 00:33:14,902
I'll go home and dig around my closet.

491
00:33:14,903 --> 00:33:17,709
- I'm counting on you.
- Okay.

492
00:33:20,333 --> 00:33:22,688
Those steamed ribs look delicious.

493
00:33:24,217 --> 00:33:25,806
Have a bite.

494
00:33:29,891 --> 00:33:31,622
It's perfect.

495
00:33:34,338 --> 00:33:35,954
Should I...

496
00:33:35,955 --> 00:33:40,043
- sleep here tonight?
- No, my friends are coming over.

497
00:33:40,044 --> 00:33:41,465
Friends?

498
00:33:41,466 --> 00:33:45,101
- Like who?
- Ah, just some girlfriends.

499
00:33:46,264 --> 00:33:48,377
Female friends.

500
00:33:50,268 --> 00:33:51,407
Really?

501
00:33:51,408 --> 00:33:54,666
I went to Ara's Facebook this afternoon,
and she seems to be doing well.

502
00:33:54,667 --> 00:33:56,766
I noticed she made a lot
of American friends too.

503
00:33:56,767 --> 00:33:58,278
Yeah.

504
00:33:58,847 --> 00:34:02,972
Since Ara's not here,
can't you move into my place?

505
00:34:03,844 --> 00:34:05,200
What about marriage?

506
00:34:05,809 --> 00:34:07,651
You want to get married again?

507
00:34:07,652 --> 00:34:10,564
You want to live together
when we're not even married?

508
00:34:10,565 --> 00:34:13,128
That's comfortable for both of us.

509
00:34:13,657 --> 00:34:15,534
You should live alone
if you want to be comfortable.

510
00:34:15,535 --> 00:34:17,604
Why would you want to live with someone?

511
00:34:22,788 --> 00:34:24,850
No, come a bit later.

512
00:34:33,790 --> 00:34:35,364
I'm going to go.

513
00:34:35,365 --> 00:34:36,796
Wait.

514
00:34:40,102 --> 00:34:42,983
Take these steamed ribs
with you and eat them at home.

515
00:34:42,984 --> 00:34:44,438
What about that?

516
00:34:44,439 --> 00:34:46,520
These are for my friends.

517
00:34:46,521 --> 00:34:48,029
Your female friends?

518
00:34:48,030 --> 00:34:49,381
Yeah.

519
00:34:50,651 --> 00:34:52,406
See you later.

520
00:34:54,165 --> 00:34:55,517
Chairman Park.

521
00:34:56,317 --> 00:35:01,098
We plan on firing Cha Ki Young with
the upcoming company reorganization.

522
00:35:01,099 --> 00:35:02,740
And?

523
00:35:02,741 --> 00:35:04,546
Please let go of your anger now.

524
00:35:04,547 --> 00:35:06,694
I know you took your ads out
because of Cha Ki Young.

525
00:35:06,695 --> 00:35:09,622
Please come back and
do business with us again.

526
00:35:09,623 --> 00:35:12,133
That was a long time ago.

527
00:35:12,134 --> 00:35:17,598
Our news station went into a deep financial
crisis after you took your ads out, Sir.

528
00:35:18,574 --> 00:35:22,122
Frankly, we don't have the power
to hold on anymore.

529
00:35:22,977 --> 00:35:28,003
It might be better if your company took
over our station. What do you think, Sir?

530
00:35:28,004 --> 00:35:30,738
I'm a businessman. I'm only concerned
about selling my products.

531
00:35:30,739 --> 00:35:33,395
I'm a not a news person!

532
00:35:33,396 --> 00:35:35,101
Chairman Park.

533
00:35:36,891 --> 00:35:38,702
Sir!

534
00:35:38,703 --> 00:35:41,923
Are you really going to leave
your junior high and dry?

535
00:35:48,142 --> 00:35:51,183
We'll go ahead and work with you
because Eun Cha kept pressuring us.

536
00:35:51,184 --> 00:35:54,109
Honestly though, I'm really worried.

537
00:35:54,110 --> 00:35:56,608
I mean, it's not the first time
you screwed up.

538
00:35:57,447 --> 00:36:00,025
It's been quite a while
since you've been an MC.

539
00:36:00,026 --> 00:36:03,506
I'm going to get fired if I don't
pull through with this program.

540
00:36:03,507 --> 00:36:07,565
And my child and I will have to live
on the streets if that happens.

541
00:36:09,794 --> 00:36:13,385
I promise to do well.
Please trust me.

542
00:36:17,894 --> 00:36:22,586
Somehow, I feel like I can relate to you
from hearing your brutal honesty.

543
00:36:22,587 --> 00:36:25,919
Okay, let's all do our best
with Cha Ki Young.

544
00:36:25,920 --> 00:36:27,542
Please take care of us.

545
00:36:27,543 --> 00:36:29,758
- I think it's going to turn out well.
- Please take care of me.

546
00:36:29,759 --> 00:36:31,201
Fighting!

547
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:43,212
Hello.

548
00:36:44,906 --> 00:36:46,547
Hello.

549
00:37:20,993 --> 00:37:22,405
Hello?

550
00:37:22,406 --> 00:37:24,104
<i>This is the writer for the fashion show.</i>

551
00:37:24,105 --> 00:37:27,242
<i>Please give me your email address
so I can send you the script.</i>

552
00:37:27,243 --> 00:37:30,794
Sure. I'll text it to you.

553
00:37:40,064 --> 00:37:42,141
Madam, hello!

554
00:37:42,142 --> 00:37:44,460
- It's been a long time.
- Yes, it has.

555
00:37:46,602 --> 00:37:49,617
Isn't the membership fee
for this place ridiculous?

556
00:37:49,618 --> 00:37:54,345
Getting in is more difficult than the cost.
Not unless you're a royal family.

557
00:37:54,346 --> 00:37:58,253
As always, a woman has to be smart catching
the right man instead of just being smart.

558
00:37:58,909 --> 00:38:03,845
Smart women are too busy trying to build an
impressive resume and compete against men.

559
00:38:03,846 --> 00:38:06,243
They can't buy a decent house
in Seoul even after a decade.

560
00:38:06,244 --> 00:38:09,836
You... got everything in one shot.

561
00:38:09,837 --> 00:38:13,184
You're the winner compared to
all those arrogant spinsters.

562
00:38:13,185 --> 00:38:15,261
Give me some dating advice.

563
00:38:15,262 --> 00:38:17,426
On how to marry a rich man.

564
00:38:18,522 --> 00:38:20,488
Hello, Ma'am.

565
00:38:20,489 --> 00:38:22,862
Oh my, aren't you
Chairman Park's daughter-in-law?

566
00:38:22,863 --> 00:38:26,948
My mother-in-law and I were thinking
about going to your boutique.

567
00:38:26,949 --> 00:38:29,979
I was really busy preparing
the fashion show.

568
00:38:29,980 --> 00:38:33,501
I sent an invitation to your mother-in-law,
so make sure you both come, okay?

569
00:38:33,502 --> 00:38:35,257
Yes Ma'am.

570
00:38:40,960 --> 00:38:43,902
That was Designer Oh Shin Hee.
Don't you know who she is?

571
00:38:43,903 --> 00:38:45,809
Of course I know who she is!

572
00:38:46,654 --> 00:38:48,723
I totally love her clothes.

573
00:38:48,724 --> 00:38:51,720
I only have one outfit of hers.
It's so expensive.

574
00:38:51,721 --> 00:38:54,312
Make sure you take me with you
to the fashion show, okay?

575
00:38:54,313 --> 00:38:56,426
Well... we'll see.

576
00:38:57,617 --> 00:39:00,946
<i>[Cubs Village Fathers' Day Visit!]</i>

577
00:39:03,316 --> 00:39:04,791
Chan!

578
00:39:04,792 --> 00:39:07,728
I'm sorry! Did you wait too long?

579
00:39:07,729 --> 00:39:09,867
My precious baby,
let me take a look at you.

580
00:39:10,936 --> 00:39:12,910
Did you eat?

581
00:39:15,079 --> 00:39:17,977
- Are you upset because I came late?
- Yes.

582
00:39:19,112 --> 00:39:20,769
I'm sorry.

583
00:39:24,579 --> 00:39:26,214
Excuse me.

584
00:39:27,401 --> 00:39:29,841
We have a Fathers' Day visit tomorrow.

585
00:39:29,842 --> 00:39:32,973
- What would you like to do about Dan?
- What is that?

586
00:39:32,974 --> 00:39:36,774
It's a party where the fathers
come and play with their children.

587
00:39:39,296 --> 00:39:42,628
I think it might be best if
Dan took the day off tomorrow.

588
00:39:42,629 --> 00:39:46,465
I have an important matter to take care of
tomorrow so he has to be here.

589
00:39:50,520 --> 00:39:53,467
I prick him with a needle
and there's not even a drop of blood.

590
00:39:53,974 --> 00:39:55,888
I mentioned how we attended
the same high school

591
00:39:55,888 --> 00:39:58,051
and Chairman Park
still wouldn't budge.

592
00:39:58,742 --> 00:40:01,366
Ho Pyung, is the company
in that bad of a situation?

593
00:40:01,367 --> 00:40:04,698
In just the first half of the year alone,
we had a deficit of 20 billion won.

594
00:40:04,699 --> 00:40:07,782
It'll be a 50 billion won deficit if
we go into the second half of the year.

595
00:40:07,783 --> 00:40:09,283
Just hang in there a little longer.

596
00:40:09,989 --> 00:40:11,642
Once I get elected...

597
00:40:11,643 --> 00:40:14,057
Are you adding fuel to fire right now?

598
00:40:14,058 --> 00:40:16,688
Do you have to leave at this critical time?

599
00:40:16,689 --> 00:40:21,322
I'm much more beneficial to you
as a politician than a news anchor.

600
00:40:21,323 --> 00:40:23,156
Just wait until I get that
gold badge pinned on my suit.

601
00:40:23,157 --> 00:40:25,925
You think I'll let the news station
fall into ruins like this?

602
00:40:25,926 --> 00:40:28,202
It doesn't have to be Chairman Park.

603
00:40:28,203 --> 00:40:30,994
I'll rake in every nickel and dime
from all those tycoons.

604
00:40:30,995 --> 00:40:32,595
Don't worry.

605
00:40:32,596 --> 00:40:37,459
All you have to do is give me
your full support with my campaign.

606
00:40:37,460 --> 00:40:41,047
I ran into Cha Ki Young today
at the news station.

607
00:40:41,048 --> 00:40:42,395
Is that so?

608
00:40:42,973 --> 00:40:45,152
I saw a picture of her son.

609
00:40:45,153 --> 00:40:49,912
I thought she would give birth
to a monster from her sperm donation.

610
00:40:51,492 --> 00:40:53,788
But he looks exactly like us.

611
00:40:53,789 --> 00:40:56,193
He was quite good-looking.

612
00:40:56,710 --> 00:41:01,938
By the way, you're sure
Tae Yun is not the father?

613
00:41:01,939 --> 00:41:05,731
Of course. She got pregnant
from a sperm donation.

614
00:41:10,702 --> 00:41:12,907
Goodness, what is this?

615
00:41:14,527 --> 00:41:17,699
It's yongbong stew, Father.
I learned it from the culinary school.

616
00:41:18,228 --> 00:41:20,702
They say all the kings
used to eat this in the past.

617
00:41:20,703 --> 00:41:22,966
I was told this is a good dish for elders
recovering their energy to eat.

618
00:41:22,967 --> 00:41:24,373
Is that so?

619
00:41:27,942 --> 00:41:32,832
Ah Mother, Madam Oh Shin Hee
is holding her fashion show tomorrow.

620
00:41:32,833 --> 00:41:35,916
She sent me an invitation last week.

621
00:41:35,917 --> 00:41:39,556
Isn't Oh Shin Hee the wife of
Assemblyman Kim Pal Soon?

622
00:41:39,557 --> 00:41:42,045
Her clothes are ridiculously expensive.

623
00:41:42,046 --> 00:41:43,329
Yes.

624
00:41:43,330 --> 00:41:47,703
The elections are coming up soon and he's
using his wife's fashion show as an excuse.

625
00:41:47,704 --> 00:41:49,781
He's trying to get political funds.

626
00:41:49,782 --> 00:41:52,567
You two might as well buy her clothes
since I'm making a hefty donation.

627
00:41:53,172 --> 00:41:54,970
Okay.

628
00:41:57,842 --> 00:42:00,624
It's very good. Sit down and join us.

629
00:42:00,625 --> 00:42:04,825
That's okay, Father.
I'll just take my time and eat later.

630
00:42:09,169 --> 00:42:11,853
<i>[Fathers' Day Visit!]</i>

631
00:42:16,356 --> 00:42:18,169
Where are the other children?

632
00:42:18,170 --> 00:42:21,549
They all went out to prepare
for the fathers' day event.

633
00:42:21,550 --> 00:42:23,865
What about Dan then?

634
00:42:23,866 --> 00:42:27,102
He doesn't have a father. How...

635
00:42:29,486 --> 00:42:33,374
So, today was a day that children without
fathers shouldn't have come, is that it?

636
00:42:34,191 --> 00:42:35,927
It's not that...

637
00:42:38,025 --> 00:42:41,737
Then you should have been
frank with me yesterday!

638
00:42:43,056 --> 00:42:46,227
I didn't want to say this to you...

639
00:42:47,147 --> 00:42:49,269
but you're really cruel!

640
00:42:49,889 --> 00:42:52,503
When the other children are laughing
and playing with their fathers...

641
00:42:53,077 --> 00:42:55,517
What is Dan supposed to do?

642
00:42:56,291 --> 00:42:59,627
What are we to do when
Dan is sad and down...

643
00:43:19,794 --> 00:43:23,122
Excuse me...
are you a member of Club Jaekwon?

644
00:43:24,196 --> 00:43:25,476
Yes.

645
00:43:25,477 --> 00:43:27,691
Ah yes, please have a seat.

646
00:43:39,260 --> 00:43:41,956
Are you the person that
came for the blind date?

647
00:43:41,957 --> 00:43:43,493
Of course!

648
00:43:45,570 --> 00:43:47,662
If you don't mind me asking,
how old are you?

649
00:43:47,663 --> 00:43:51,957
I'm not that old!
I'm only 50 years old!

650
00:43:51,958 --> 00:43:53,451
50 years old.

651
00:43:54,809 --> 00:43:57,247
Then it won't be too long until
you celebrate your 60th birthday.

652
00:43:58,020 --> 00:44:01,999
I'm trying to find a partner I can share
the last remaining years of my life with.

653
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:05,022
Last... remaining years?

654
00:44:05,023 --> 00:44:08,419
After my late wife died of
cancer three years ago...

655
00:44:09,251 --> 00:44:11,267
I was really, truly lonely.

656
00:44:11,806 --> 00:44:15,366
I thought it was time to open myself up
and share my life with someone again.

657
00:44:21,207 --> 00:44:22,870
I have two sons.

658
00:44:22,871 --> 00:44:26,853
One moved out after he got hired.

659
00:44:26,854 --> 00:44:31,327
The other rascal married early
and I even have a grandchild now.

660
00:44:32,945 --> 00:44:36,473
You won't have to lift
a finger if you marry me.

661
00:44:36,474 --> 00:44:38,631
- Hold on, I need to go to the restroom.
- Sure.

662
00:44:40,586 --> 00:44:42,516
The restroom is over there.

663
00:44:50,358 --> 00:44:52,533
Seriously, I'm going crazy!

664
00:45:06,073 --> 00:45:07,719
Let's go.

665
00:45:08,746 --> 00:45:10,326
Aren't you busy?

666
00:45:10,327 --> 00:45:12,569
Isn't the fashion show today?

667
00:45:13,342 --> 00:45:15,188
Anchor Jo.

668
00:45:15,189 --> 00:45:17,759
I can't do the fashion show.

669
00:45:17,760 --> 00:45:21,656
I know this is a huge inconvenience but you
should find someone to replace me quickly.

670
00:45:21,657 --> 00:45:23,039
What the heck are you saying right now?

671
00:45:23,040 --> 00:45:26,501
I have to be with Dan
at that time somewhere.

672
00:45:27,410 --> 00:45:29,067
Are you crazy?

673
00:45:29,068 --> 00:45:31,299
The news station is your bread and butter.

674
00:45:31,300 --> 00:45:33,950
And you're telling me you're going
to bail the show because of your son?

675
00:45:35,115 --> 00:45:37,643
- I'm sorry.
- I'll keep it short.

676
00:45:37,644 --> 00:45:40,340
Turn in your resignation right now if
you're not going to host the fashion show.

677
00:45:40,341 --> 00:45:42,679
Do you think the news station
is a child welfare foundation?

678
00:45:42,680 --> 00:45:43,913
You don't even work!

679
00:45:43,914 --> 00:45:47,005
Why does the station have to pay
you to raise your kid?

680
00:45:48,828 --> 00:45:50,413
Mom.

681
00:45:50,414 --> 00:45:53,167
Please lower your voice!
Dan can hear you!

682
00:45:53,168 --> 00:45:56,064
Just how long are you
going to live in hiding?

683
00:45:56,065 --> 00:45:58,982
Where did that high and mighty
attitude of yours go to?

684
00:46:01,084 --> 00:46:02,927
I'm sorry.

685
00:46:04,592 --> 00:46:07,317
Cha Dan, I'm not angry.

686
00:46:07,318 --> 00:46:10,632
A man's voice is always supposed
to be loud if he wants to succeed in life!

687
00:46:10,633 --> 00:46:13,487
Convince your mom and send her
to the fashion show. Understood?

688
00:46:33,318 --> 00:46:35,387
Hey, Bro!

689
00:46:36,152 --> 00:46:39,994
I heard you replaced Kang Ha Ni with
Cha Ki Young for Oh Shin Hee's fashion show?

690
00:46:39,995 --> 00:46:41,590
Yeah. Why?

691
00:46:41,591 --> 00:46:44,888
You know her husband is
Assemblyman Kim Pal Soon, right?

692
00:46:44,889 --> 00:46:46,182
Of course I know!

693
00:46:46,183 --> 00:46:50,862
And I know that he's nominated unofficially
as the chairman for the ruling party.

694
00:46:50,863 --> 00:46:56,099
Did you also know that Kim Pal Soon
is the president of the

695
00:46:56,100 --> 00:46:58,346
'Men Are of the Heavens and
Women Are of the Earth' club?

696
00:46:58,892 --> 00:47:00,036
Really?

697
00:47:00,037 --> 00:47:01,926
You're having a single mother
host a fashion show

698
00:47:01,927 --> 00:47:06,683
of the wife of the most macho man
in the National Assembly?

699
00:47:06,684 --> 00:47:11,270
You're going to be a great politician
with that brain of yours, you idiot.

700
00:47:20,673 --> 00:47:25,966
Kang Ha Ni, dress up and come
to the fashion show right now! Right now!

701
00:47:28,319 --> 00:47:30,613
Seriously, I'm going to go nuts!

702
00:47:30,614 --> 00:47:33,046
<i>Will the models please enter.</i>

703
00:47:36,528 --> 00:47:38,657
<i>Walk down the runway.</i>

704
00:47:41,125 --> 00:47:43,470
<i>Please continue.</i>

705
00:47:44,240 --> 00:47:45,660
Cha Ki Young.

706
00:47:45,661 --> 00:47:48,438
I got an urgent order
from the company just now.

707
00:47:48,439 --> 00:47:51,336
We need to switch MCs.

708
00:47:51,337 --> 00:47:53,696
- Excuse me?
- I'm so sorry.

709
00:47:53,697 --> 00:47:56,717
Anchor Jo Eun Cha will explain
all the details to you.

710
00:47:59,915 --> 00:48:01,354
I understand.

711
00:48:02,339 --> 00:48:03,570
Wait.

712
00:48:03,571 --> 00:48:06,310
Give me the script and
cue cards before you leave.

713
00:48:08,259 --> 00:48:10,582
Thank you. Here you go, Miss Ha Ni.

714
00:48:13,621 --> 00:48:16,975
I'm sorry, but let's start the rehearsal
over with Announcer Kang Ha Ni.

715
00:48:16,976 --> 00:48:19,261
I understand. Okay, start the music over!

716
00:48:23,957 --> 00:48:25,704
Cha Ki Young, I'm sorry.

717
00:48:25,705 --> 00:48:29,667
It was the President's order. I'll find
a better program for you to take over.

718
00:48:29,668 --> 00:48:31,818
The fashion show is just a one time deal.

719
00:48:31,819 --> 00:48:35,824
That's okay. Just help me not to get fired.

720
00:48:35,825 --> 00:48:38,251
Okay! I can do that!

721
00:48:40,679 --> 00:48:43,060
Where are you going to go now?

722
00:48:43,061 --> 00:48:45,664
- To Dan's daycare.
- At this hour?

723
00:48:45,665 --> 00:48:48,513
All the fathers are invited to
come visit their children today.

724
00:48:48,514 --> 00:48:51,783
I declined the fashion show
because of that reason.

725
00:48:52,584 --> 00:48:54,361
It turned out well since I got the boot.

726
00:48:54,362 --> 00:48:56,182
I'll talk to you later.

727
00:49:00,337 --> 00:49:03,857
Jo Eun Cha. You really are a rotten jerk.

728
00:49:03,858 --> 00:49:06,859
You convinced her to be the fashion show MC
and then replaced her with Kang Ha Ni.

729
00:49:06,860 --> 00:49:10,055
You're a two-faced liar.
Nothing but complete trash.

730
00:49:10,056 --> 00:49:13,819
Good for nothing trash!
Trash, trash, trash!

731
00:49:18,123 --> 00:49:19,507
Daycare?

732
00:49:19,508 --> 00:49:23,617
<i>First, let's introduce each
father that came to visit.</i>

733
00:49:23,618 --> 00:49:26,712
<i>- Please introduce yourselves.
- I'm Kim Yoo Ki's father.</i>

734
00:49:28,359 --> 00:49:29,759
<i>The next person please.</i>

735
00:49:29,760 --> 00:49:32,343
<i>Yes, I'm Bo Na's father.</i>

736
00:49:34,395 --> 00:49:36,637
<i>I'm Mi Jae's dad.</i>

737
00:49:39,021 --> 00:49:41,156
- Dan!
- Mom.

738
00:49:41,763 --> 00:49:44,069
Ms. Cha, you came!

739
00:49:44,742 --> 00:49:47,463
Dan, let's go home.

740
00:49:50,913 --> 00:49:53,129
- You want to do that?
- Yeah.

741
00:49:54,442 --> 00:49:55,883
Really?

742
00:49:55,884 --> 00:50:01,237
- Who's your dad again?
